1

). Pygophore oblong, ventral surface clothed with long setae, median process with a sharp process on each side (
Figs. 3, 4
); paramere clubbed, bent, subapical portion slightly thickened, apically rounded, with many long setae of different lengths (
Figs. 5, 6
